programme.title: The Defiled: We Are All Meat
programme.desc: In a post apocalyptic world, science and technology have backfired leaving unfathomable destruction and a permanently diseased planet in its wake. A virus is mutating the human race turning innocent survivors into mindless cannibals. In a savage future world devoid of hope, a man infected with the deadly viral disease must cope with the burden of a new born son, ensuring his survival. Though he is infected, he does not allow his growing desire for human flesh to overcome his responsibility to the newborn. Along the road, traveling from town to town, he saves an unaffected woman from a certain death by facing down her perpetrators. Ultimately she joins him on his odyssey, a journey through hell on earth in search of a safe haven in which they can perhaps start a life together, both becoming committed to doing whatever it takes to make sure the child survives. Reminiscent of the work of Lynch, Maddin and Tarkovsky, The Defiled is a black and white epic of unparalleled artistry examining life, death and the ultimate sacrifice of love. Not since Carnival of Souls and Night of the Living Dead has a film captured the surreal outer dimensions of the human condition.

programme.title: Western Hunting & Conservation Expo / Our Wyld Life / EP1
programme.desc:
Welcome to Our Wyld Life where host Kristy Titus and her husband, Yogi, take viewers along on their day-to-day lives, full of adventure. After relocating to Wyoming, hunting, outdoor and shooting sports recreation are literally in their backyard. The couple is truly making their home on the range while developing their new homestead and enjoying life in the cowboy state.
In our premiere episode, we show you a little bit of what it's like being a Wyoming resident, in the winter. After a tough start, Kristy makes it a great week with familiar faces and many new ones, in what is one of the most fun shows of the year! If you didn't make it in 2023, it's a must to attend next year! Also, you'll be introduced to the newest (and longest eared) members of the family! Kristy shows off her baby mules...lots more of the mules to come! When they aren't out on an adventure trekking deep into the backcountry with their horses and mules, you'll find them preparing for the next opportunity to do so.
Our Wyld Life presents the journey of life out west in Wyoming.

The Killpatrick family led by husband and father Michael is paving the way for the next generation of regenerative farming. This farm sprouted from the 2020 pandemic and in a few short years has become a pivotal cornerstone of their city community for all things holistic and organic. The Farm on Central is proving what can be accomplished with dedication to the future of farming.

programme.title: Farm Hero
programme.desc: On this episode, Laura takes a trip to White Oak Pastures in Georgia to meet with pioneer and visionary, Will Harris. After two decades of monocultural farming, Will took his multi-generation farm into a completely new direction by turning it into a regenerative farm. Through trials and tribulations, Will and his family are paving the way for regenerative agriculture and educating the public on the importance of food education.

programme.desc: Mike McCommas acts as point man to the FBI's case against the Arizona Patriots, a white supremacist group. McCommas discovers that the gang is plotting an armored car heist and planning to kill the drivers before escaping into the desert. The group may have pulled it off were it not for McCommas living with them for eight months, and preventing the heist and murders the day before they go down.

programme.title: Operation Insurance Scam Artist: Arson For Hire
programme.desc: Free-lance undercover detective Bob Cerrone is hired by a Denver insurance company to investigate a series of insurance claims. During his investigation, Cerrone is solicited by the insured to rob his office, sink a boat, and lastly, to burn down a row house he owns. When Cerrone protests that there are people living in the apartments, he is told, "I don't care." The detective gets it all on tape and the man is arrested for solicitation of arson.

programme.title: Operation Con Cino: Rocky Mountain High
programme.desc: Denver cop Joe Padilla infiltrates a thriving drug crew in the center of the Rocky Mountains. Padilla is nearly shot during one exchange but continues to do deals as he goes up the drug dealing food chain. Padilla steals a car load of cocaine and corners the traffickers in an outrageous heist and takedown that for a time, halts the flow of drugs in Denver.

McCommas discovers that the gang is plotting an armored car heist and planning to kill the drivers before escaping into the desert. The group may have pulled it off were it not for McCommas living with them for eight months, and preventing the heist and murders the day before they go down.

programme.title: Operation Insurance Scam Artist: Arson For Hire
programme.desc: Free-lance undercover detective Bob Cerrone is hired by a Denver insurance company to investigate a series of insurance claims. During his investigation, Cerrone is solicited by the insured to rob his office, sink a boat, and lastly, to burn down a row house he owns. When Cerrone protests that there are people living in the apartments, he is told, "I don't care." The detective gets it all on tape and the man is arrested for solicitation of arson.

programme.title: Operation Con Cino: Rocky Mountain High
programme.desc: Denver cop Joe Padilla infiltrates a thriving drug crew in the center of the Rocky Mountains. Padilla is nearly shot during one exchange but continues to do deals as he goes up the drug dealing food chain. Padilla steals a car load of cocaine and corners the traffickers in an outrageous heist and takedown that for a time, halts the flow of drugs in Denver.
